v1.30.0 - full-text search via Postgres tsvector

Schema: generated tsvector columns + GIN indexes on Task, Comment, Project.
simple text-search config (no stemming) because TaskHub content is heavily
Persian. setweight('A') on title, setweight('B') on description so title
hits outrank description-heavy hits at the same term frequency.

Backend: GET /api/search runs three parameterised raw queries (one per
bucket) with plainto_tsquery + ts_headline + ts_rank. Tenant isolation
via teamMembership.findMany; results restricted to teams the caller is a
member of. No global-ADMIN bypass. Soft-deleted tasks/comments excluded.
Per-bucket keyset cursor on (rank, id) with explicit ::real cast for
correct float4 tiebreak. Cap 50 per page, default 20.

Frontend: top-nav SearchInput (Enter-to-submit, sm+ visible) + /search
results page with three buckets and per-bucket Load more. Excerpts
render ts_headline output through a sanitiser that allows only <b>/</b>.
EN + FA i18n.

Tests: 11 new integration tests cover basic match (title/comment/project),
title-weighted ranking, cross-team isolation (critical), soft-delete
exclusion, per-bucket keyset pagination across 25 same-keyword rows,
type filter, empty q short-circuit, no-membership empty buckets, 401
for anonymous callers. Full suite 258 passed, 5 skipped (LDAP-only).

Phase boundary: simple config trades english stemming for Persian
correctness; per-instance config setting is a v1.31 follow-up.